    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-21T02:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-21T02:35:00-05:00" n="626"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d626">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.9131/133: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-21T11:00:00+03:25"
                            >December 21, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:19 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>275. Referring to the Legation’s telegram No. 265, December 5, 2 p.m., the Prime
                    Minister and the Acting Minister for Foreign Affairs on the occasion of my
                    official calls and the Shah himself when <pb facs="0705" n="693" xml:id="pg_693"
                    /> I presented my letter of credence all pointedly expressed interest in the
                    early conclusion of the trade agreement.</p>
                <p>Report<note n="92" xml:id="d626fn92">Submitted as an enclosure to despatch No. 8,
                        December 23, 1940, from the Minister in Iran; not printed.</note> called for
                    in Department’s 119, November 19, 5 p.m. will be forwarded in the next pouch,
                    December 28, for transmission via trans-Atlantic airmail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
